   Honestly I havent worked with a 4 inch pan before. So I calculated pan
   volume measurements and found out that you can use half the
   measurements of this whole recipe for two 4-inch cake pans. Or you can
   use my Chocolate Cake recipe from here
   (https://www.pepperdelight.com/chocolate-cake-with-dulce-de-leche/),
   which is equivalent to two 4-inch cake pans and pour the batter by
   giving it some it some space to rise. If there is any leftover batter,
   you can either discard it or make some cupcakes. (Please note, these
   are according to volume calculations). <p>Hello Leana, </p> <p>Honestly
