   6 Akhila Thu, 12 Sep 2019 16:39:39 +0000
   http://www.pepperdelight.com/?p=1797#comment-7506 For this Tandoori
   Chicken, I would suggest using yogurt as its the traditional way. But
   you can substitute it with buttermilk. There is no need of a second
   marination, you need to marinate chicken with yogurt along with spices
   (preferably overnight) for a flavorful chicken. <p>For this Tandoori
   Chicken, I would suggest using yogurt as its the traditional way. But
   you can substitute it with buttermilk. There is no need of a second
   marination, you need to marinate chicken with yogurt along with spices
   (preferably overnight) for a flavorful chicken.</p>
