                               Avocado Egg Toast

   Akhila

   2 years ago

   Jump to Recipe Print Recipe

   Healthy Avocado Toast‚Ä¶ A Protein Packed Breakfast with Eggs and
   Avocado‚Ä¶!!! Simple, Nutritious, & Perfect for any meal of your day‚Ä¶ All
   in 10 minutes‚Ä¶

   Rain, Rain, Rain‚Ä¶ it‚Äôs been raining crazy for the last two weeks and I
   just feel like crawling under my blanket, stay warm n cozy, and  sleep
   a lot more. Do you guys feel the same on rainy days? And when you wake
   up, you wish to have a hot piping cup of coffee and a warm breakfast,
   ready on the table‚Ä¶ I would love to have a toast with sides for
   breakfast!

   My regular breakfast menu is mostly of Indian dishes; either some sort
   of a savory crepe, or steamed rice/wheat cakes. Although they are rich
   and healthy, they are not a good choice for a lazy morning. Smoothies
   and cereals are our go-to options for a quick breakfast, even eggs; my
   husband does eggs many ways and they turn out pretty good always. He
   loves eggs and has a couple of tricks up his sleeve to quickly cook
   eggs, be it poached, hard boiled, fried, or even microwaved!! So when
   it comes to any egg based recipes I am experimenting with, I leave the
   eggs with him; Of course I want them to look perfect in my recipe
   photos, and I know that he being a perfectionist does a wonderful job
   with the cooking and presentation!!

   So this recipe is yummy and simple, there is hardly any recipe to speak
   about. All you need are:
     * Sliced bread ‚Äì toasted, any variety would work.
     * Eggs ‚Äì poached or fried, but keep the yolks runny.
     * Avocadoes ‚Äì sliced.
     * Seasoning ‚Äì salt and pepper.

   This warm n crunchy toast is a perfect dish for any meal of the day and
   you can try out wide varieties of it with different toppings of your
   choice.

   Enjoy, Happy Cooking!!!

